Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so if there are two coins ABC and XYZ, both not that active, then odds of two people who want to do the opposite of each others ABC <-> XYZ trade is very unlikely

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: however, with liquid KMD markets, you can convert ABC to KMD and KMD to XYZ, and the other party can independently do the reverse

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the net buying pressure on KMD is neutral, just more usage and this is the value creation

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: being used as the intermediate coin in a swap, that alone creates value for KMD

Author: Gateway#3763

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: KMD becomes the coin to park funds in. then if a good deal is available in ABC (or XYZ) you can grab it. having any other coin than KMD means you are "farther away"

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: all swaps are using transparent addresses

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: that being said, there is no KYC needed and all that is known is the pubkey
